      "id": 1,
      "text": "Saddle Rock Grist Mill, an 18th‑century landmark, sits on the Great Neck Peninsula and is a quick stop for history buffs and photographers.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.longislandguide.com/visit/great-neck/"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Before it was called Great Neck Gardens, the area was historically known as Madnan's Neck.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Great_Neck_Gardens%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Great Neck Gardens has never been incorporated, so it is governed directly by the Town of North Hempstead.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        21,
        25
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia",
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Great_Neck_Gardens%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The Gold Coast Arts Center, a long‑standing venue, hosts film screenings, concerts, exhibits, and classes throughout the year.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.longislandguide.com/visit/great-neck/"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Great Neck Plaza, centered around the LIRR station, is the peninsula’s most walkable downtown with cafés, bakeries, and shops.",
